work.work-title: For the beauty of the earth

credit.credit-words: For the beauty of each hour, Of the day and of the night, Hill and vale, and tree and flower, Sun and moon, and stars of light.
For the joy of human love, Brother, sister, parent, child, Friends on earth and friends above, For all gentle thoughts and mild.
Lord of all, to Thee we raise, This our hymn of grateful praise.
For the beauty of the earth
For Thy Church, that evermore Lifteth holy hands above, Offering up on every shore Her pure sacrifice of love.

direction-type.words: For the glory of the skies,
of earth and buds of Heaven.
